a(S'Amnesia[edit]'
p8670
g2
tp8671
a(S'Some symptoms of amnesia have been shown to be alleviated through '
p8672
g2
tp8673
a(S'various interactions with music, including playing and listening. One such '
p8674
g2
tp8675
a(S'case is that of Clive Wearing, whose severe retrograde and anterograde '
p8676
g2
tp8677
a(S'amnesia have been detailed in the documentaries Prisoner of '
p8678
g2
tp8679
a(S'Consciousness and The Man with the 7 Second Memory. Though unable to '
p8680
g2
tp8681
a(S'recall past memories or form new ones, Wearing is still able to play, conduct, '
p8682
g2
tp8683
a(S'and sing along with music learned prior to the onset of his amnesia, and '
p8684
g2
tp8685
a(S'even add improvisations and flourishes.[83]'
p8686
g2
