a(g6
g2
tp8688
a(S'Wearing s case reinforces the theory that episodic memory fundamentally '
p8689
g2
tp8690
a(S'differs from procedural or semantic memory. Sacks suggests that while '
p8691
g2
tp8692
a(S'Wearing is completely unable to recall events or episodes, musical '
p8693
g2
tp8694
a(S'performance (and the muscle memory involved) are a form of procedural '
p8695
g2
tp8696
a(S'memory that is not typically hindered in amnesia cases [Sacks]. Indeed, '
p8697
g2
tp8698
a(S'there is evidence that while episodic memory is reliant on the hippocampal '
p8699
g2
tp8700
a(S'formation, amnesiacs with damage to this area can show a loss of episodic '
p8701
g2
tp8702
a(S'memory accompanied by (partially) intact semantic memory.[84]'
