tp8735
a(S'Music therapy is used with schizophrenic patients to ameliorate many of the '
p8736
g2
tp8737
a(S'symptoms of the disorder. Individual studies of patients undergoing music '
p8738
g2
tp8739
a(S'therapy showed diminished negative symptoms such as flattened affect, '
p8740
g2
tp8741
a(S'speech issues, and anhedonia and improved social symptoms such as '
p8742
g2
tp8743
a(S'increased conversation ability, reduced social isolation, and increased '
p8744
g2
tp8745
a(S'interest in external events.[86]'
p8746
g2
tp8747
a(g6
g2
tp8748
a(S'Meta-studies have confirmed many of these results, showing that music '
p8749
g2
tp8750
a(S'therapy in conjunction with standard care to be superior to standard care '
p8751
g2
tp8752
a(S'alone. Improvements were seen in negative symptoms, general mental state, '
p8753
g2
tp8754
a(S'depression, anxiety, and even cognitive functioning. These meta-studies '
p8755
g2
tp8756
a(S'have also shown, however, that these results can be inconsistent and that '
p8757
g2
tp8758
