a(S"The only major competitor in the x86 processor market is Advanced Micro Devices (AMD), with which Intel has had full cross-licensing agreements since 1976: each partner can use the other's patented technological innovations without charge after a certain time.[11] However, the cross-licensing agreement is canceled in the event of an AMD bankruptcy or takeover.[12]"
p20283
g19085
tp20284
a(g6
g19085
