g19085
tp21137
a(S'After K8 came K10. In September 2007, AMD released the first K10 processors   nine quad-core Third Generation Opteron processors   followed in November by the Phenom processor for desktop. K10 processors came in dual-core, triple-core,[115] and quad-core versions, with all cores on a single die. AMD released a new platform, codenamed "Spider", which utilized the new Phenom processor, as well as an R770 GPU and a 790 GX/FX chipset from the AMD 700 chipset series. However, AMD built the Spider at 65nm, which was uncompetitive with Intel\'s smaller and more power-efficient 45nm.'
p21138
