a(S'In April 2010, AMD released a new Phenom II hexa-core (6-core) processor codenamed "Thuban". This was a totally new die based on the hexa-core  Istanbul  Opteron processor. It included AMD\'s  turbo core  technology, which allows the processor to automatically switch from 6 cores to 3 faster cores when more pure speed is needed. AMD\'s enthusiast platform, codenamed "Leo", utilized the new Phenom II, a new chipset from the AMD 800 chipset series and an ATI  Cypress  GPU from the Evergreen GPU series.'
