a(S'Llano was AMD\'s first APU built for laptops. Llano was the second APU released,[117] targeted at the mainstream market.[116] Incorporating a CPU and GPU on the same die, as well as northbridge functions, and using "Socket FM1" with DDR3 memory. The CPU part of the processor was based on the Phenom II "Deneb" processor. AMD suffered an unexpected decrease in revenue based on production problems for the Llano.[118]'
