a(S'Jaguar is a x86-64 microarchitecture codename for a processor core that is used in various APUs from AMD aimed at the low-power/low-cost market. It is also used as the microarchitecture for the custom APUs in the PS4 and Xbox One (which contain CPU, GPU and memory).'
