a(S'Zen is a new architecture for x86-64 based CPUs and APUs, built from the ground up by a team led by Jim Keller, beginning with his arrival in 2012, and taping out before his departure in September 2015. Zen will be built on the 14 nm node and have a renewed focus on single-core performance and HSA compatibility.[126] Zen will be the first chip encompassing CPUs and APUs from AMD built for a single socket. It will also support DDR4. It is expected to be released mid-late 2016, following the availability of the AMD A10-7890K FM2+ desktop CPU.'
