a(S'Peripheral card slots[edit]'
p21660
g19085
tp21661
a(S'A typical motherboard will have a different number of connections depending on its standard and form factor.'
p21662
g19085
tp21663
a(g6
g19085
tp21664
a(S'A standard, modern ATX motherboard will typically have two or three PCI-Express 16x connection for a graphics card, one or two legacy PCI slots for various expansion cards, and one or two PCI-E 1x (which has superseded PCI). A standard EATX motherboard will have two to four PCI-E 16x connection for graphics cards, and a varying number of PCI and PCI-E 1x slots. It can sometimes also have a PCI-E 4x slot (will vary between brands and models).'
p21665
g19085
tp21666
a(g6
g19085
tp21667
a(S'Some motherboards have two or more PCI-E 16x slots, to allow more than 2 monitors without special hardware, or use a special graphics technology called SLI (for Nvidia) and Crossfire (for AMD). These allow 2 to 4 graphics cards to be linked together, to allow better performance in intensive graphical computing tasks, such as gaming, video editing, etc.'
