a(S'Main article: EDRAM'
p22409
g19085
tp22410
a(S'DRAM that is integrated into an integrated circuit designed in a logic-optimized process, such as an application-specific integrated circuit (ASIC) or a microprocessor, is called embedded DRAM (eDRAM). Embedded DRAM requires DRAM cell designs that can be fabricated without preventing the fabrication of fast-switching transistors used in high-performance logic, and modification of the basic logic-optimized process technology to accommodate the process steps required to build DRAM cell structures.'
