a(S'DRAM can be divided into asynchronous and synchronous DRAM. In addition, graphics DRAM is specially designed for graphics tasks, and can be asynchronous or synchronous DRAM in nature. Pseudostatic RAM (PSRAM) have an architecture and interface that closely mimics the operation and interface of static RAM. Lastly, 1T DRAM uses a capacitorless design, as opposed to the usual 1T/1C (one transistor/one capacitor) designs of conventional DRAM.'
