a(S'Principles of operation[edit]'
p22863
g19085
tp22864
a(S'Flash memory stores information in an array of memory cells made from floating-gate transistors. In single-level cell (SLC) devices, each cell stores only one bit of information. In multi-level cell (MLC) devices, including triple-level cell (TLC) devices, can store more than one bit per cell.'
