a(S'Writing and erasing[edit]'
p22936
g19085
tp22937
a(S'NAND flash uses tunnel injection for writing and tunnel release for erasing. NAND flash memory forms the core of the removable USB storage devices known as USB flash drives, as well as most memory card formats and solid-state drives available today.'
p22938
