a(S'Dedicated vs integrated graphics[edit]'
p23380
g19085
tp23381
a(g6
g19085
tp23382
a(S'Classical desktop computer architecture with a distinct graphics card over PCI Express. Typical bandwidths for given memory technologies, missing are the memory latency. Zero-copy between GPU and CPU is not possible, since both have their distinct physical memories. Data must be copied from one to the other to be shared.'
p23383
