g19085
tp24292
a(S'Machine languages and the assembly languages that represent them (collectively termed low level programming languages) tend to be unique to a particular type of computer. For instance, an ARM architecture computer (such as may be found in a PDA or a hand held videogame) cannot understand the machine language of an Intel Pentium or the AMD Athlon 64 computer that might be in a PC.[59]'
p24293
