p25127
g19085
tp25128
a(S'on differences in the programming facilities provided by the different platforms, including hardware and operating system resources, expected behavior of the hardware '
p25129
g19085
tp25130
a(S'and operating system, and availability of platform specific compilers (and sometimes libraries) for the language of the source code.'
p25131
g19085
tp25132
a(S'Maintainability: the ease with which a program can be modified by its present or future developers in order to make improvements or customizations, fix bugs and security '
p25133
g19085
tp25134
a(S'holes, or adapt it to new environments. Good practices during initial development make the difference in this regard. This quality may not be directly apparent to the end '
p25135
g19085
tp25136
a(S'user but it can significantly affect the fate of a program over the long term.'
p25137
g19085
tp25138
a(S'Efficiency/performance: the amount of system resources a program consumes (processor time, memory space, slow devices such as disks, network bandwidth and to '
p25139
g19085
